Description: The gender of the individual (e.g., Male, Female).
The age of the individual in years.
A numeric score indicating the level of academic pressure experienced by the individual (e.g., 1 to 5 scale).
A numeric score representing how satisfied the individual is with their study routine (e.g., 1 to 5 scale).
The amount of sleep the individual gets, categorized into ranges (e.g., '5-6 hours', '7-8 hours', 'More than 8 hours').
The individual's eating habits categorized as 'Healthy,' 'Unhealthy,' or 'Moderate.'

Column Name: Have you ever had suicidal thoughts?
Description: Indicates whether the individual has had suicidal thoughts (Yes/No).

A numeric score indicating the level of financial stress experienced by the individual.
Indicates if the individual has a family history of mental illness (Yes/No).
Indicates whether the individual has been diagnosed with depression (Yes/No).
